<font color="#FF0000">CNN AND CHET &amp; MARC</font><br>
<tt>Sat May 24 23:13:33 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
Chet, I do believe I was witness today, to the birth of the next media star. I mean what an image. Clearly this is a man of trust and character, of depth and girth, who dominated the picture screen as the CNN announcer tried to talk over. What a guy. Trustworthy written all over him. Busy and at work, yet finds time to zone in on the site while at work. Hope the boss doesn't fine out.  You were good and the CNN piece good too, hope it helps in the final effort which is keeping us (the site) afloat.<br><br>
Marc, although a bit folicle challenged (note the clever use of p.c. lingo) was clear and concise as well. You both survived the media and the editorial knife quite well, and I for one, raise one (or two) for/to  you both.<br><br>
Unfortunately, exposure also brings out those that scurry away when the light is turned on. Thread #79 is so off base and intrusive, that, oh well, perhaps he can go take pictures of Swanson Photo? I already e-mailed POV about this infestation and need for the Raid Can.<br><br>
Chet, now I am one up on you and I feel bad for that. I have seen you, as have millions, but not the reverse. All I can offer in return is that after the 25th checker at the local market said (around the time of his death): &quot;Gee, you look like Jerry Garcia&quot;, that I freaked out.  Gone was the small pony tail, and in was Lady Clariol beard dye.  Modesty be damned, I did not want to look like a fat aging doper. The first two may be true, the last isn't.  So, I guess that our waists continue to expand as does our age in years, and our I.Q. in years of intelligence lived.  Good going Chet.  (and Marc). Happy Memorial Day, and to all of you vets, thank you, too, for a job well done (from the protestor no less).<br><br>
dr. crazy
